# Per-developer private-pattern list. Copy to `.privacy-patterns`
# (gitignored), then add regexes — one per line — that scripts/hooks/pre-commit
# should block in addition to its built-in patterns.
#
# Lines starting with `#` are comments. Blank lines ignored.
# Patterns are extended regular expressions (grep -E).
#
# Common additions:
#   - Your hardware serials (run `adb devices` once and copy the value)
#   - Your internal hostnames / static LAN IPs
#   - Your real name if it should never appear in commits (e.g., ABC123XYZ)
#   - Anything from a previous leak you scrubbed via filter-repo
#
# Example entries (commented out — uncomment + edit for your setup):
# ABC123XYZ
# my-laptop\.local
# user@example\.com
